# Swift Conventions

- Keep Views free of AVFoundation, GRDB, and direct file I/O.
- Coordinate observable state in `@MainActor` ViewModels.
- Values crossing isolation boundaries must be `Sendable`.
- Domain code imports Foundation only when required and never imports UI/I/O frameworks.
- Persistence and audio implementations depend inward on Domain protocols.
- Preserve actionable errors; do not use empty `catch` or `try?` for critical operations.
- Add tests for rule, state-machine, repository, or migration changes.
